27/11/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Chief of the US National Guard Bureau, Lieutenant General Steven Blum, visited Macedonia on Wednesday (26 November). In separate meetings with Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Army Chief of General Staff General Metodi Stamboliski, Blum discussed the progress of defence sector reforms, issues related to army staff reduction, and the technology needed to maintain modernised equipment.
In other news Wednesday, Interior Minister Hari Kostov, Dutch Ambassador to Macedonia Johan Wolfs and the head of the OSCE Spillover Monitor Mission to Skopje, Craig Jenness, signed an agreement on a grant that would support 11 projects involving the police. (MIA, Makfax - 26/11/03)
